Azure Policy and Governance Lab

Overview

This lab focused on implementing governance in Microsoft Azure using Azure Policy and resource tagging.

The objective was to enforce organizational standards, improve reporting, and maintain compliance across Azure resources using policies and remediation tasks.


Lab Objectives

Implement Azure governance using Azure Policy
Apply and manage resource tags
Enforce compliance using policy definitions
Understand policy remediation
Improve resource organization and reporting



Technologies Used

Microsoft Azure
Azure Policy
Azure Resource Groups
Azure Tags
Azure Policy Initiatives
Azure Portal

Lab Scenario

An organization requires all Azure resources to include a **Cost Center** tag for governance, reporting, and cost tracking purposes.

To achieve this:

A Resource Group was created
Tags were applied at the Resource Group level
Azure Policy was used to enforce mandatory tagging
Existing resources were remediated to inherit tags automatically


